******
[3] Dysentery - Armenia (Kotayk Province)
Date: Mon 1 Dec 2014
Source: ARKA News Agency [edited]
http://arka.am/en/news/incidents/dysentery_in_kids_hospitalized_with_food_poisoning_confirmed_armenian_ministry_of_health/


Dysentery in children hospitalized from the Yeghvard kindergarten on Sat 29 Nov 2014 with symptoms of foodborne [illness] was confirmed, the press office of Armenia's ministry of health reported.

The number of diseased children reached 64, according to the report. Instructed by the premier, Armen Muradyan, the minister of health visited Nairi Medical Center for preventive anti-epidemic measures. There are currently 46 hospitalized children in Nairi Medical Center, 17 in Nork Infectious Diseases Hospital in Yerevan, and one in the Holy Mother Medical Center. Another 21 children received outpatient treatment, says the report.

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>

[The etiology of the dysentery in this Armenian outbreak is not stated, nor is it entirely clear that the episode was foodborne. Bacillary dysentery caused by _Shigella_ is readily spread from child to child without it being food-associated. - Mod.LL

[A ProMED-mail HealthMap for Kotayk province, Armenia can be accessed at https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=3019124,20895.]
